6:
Ahh, hot hot hot!
Yet delicious!
10:
When you said you liked spicy food, I
had a feeling you'd be a fan of this
one, Marina.
13:
I also took the liberty of researching
other well-reviewed eateries in the
area! I was thinking we could hit
them all up one by one.
19:
That sounds like a great idea! No
better way to spend a vacation, if
you ask me.
23:
Hey, Alk. When's this kid going home,
anyway?
26:
Huh? I don't know. Why, do you want
him gone?
31:
Don't be an idiot! You know why. We
don't want the Cap'n taking to him
too much. You know how she is!
34: I have no idea what you mean.
39: I saw it with me own eyes.
42:
In the Cap'n's quarters. She had this
book. Very small.
45:
Wait a minute, why were you in her
quarters?!
49:
Barkeep! Got any ale? Preferably
somethin' cheap and strong!
53:
HUH? The Crimson Blades?! What
are you doin' here!
57:
Well, look what the cat dragged in.
You looking for a fight or what?
62:
H-here? Don't be ridiculous. We're on
land!
66:
Cap'n, are we really gonna turn tail
and run?!
70:
Even if we fought them, we've got no
chance of winning! Let's keep things
quiet.
73:
Oh come on, boss, you really gonna
be CHICKEN like that? We need to
show 'em what we're made of!
78:
Gah! Fine. It's ON! Let's settle things
once and for all, Marina!
83: Now that's what I'm talking about!
90:
Gahahaha, you can't outdrink a
grizzled pirate like me!
92:
I've got this one in the bag! There's
no way I'll lose!
94:
How's about... *hic*
You and I go on a DATE, huh?
97:
Cap'n! She's our enemy! Have you
lost your mind?
110:
Heh. All right, then. But ONLY if you
win.
120:
Well, isn't that a shame? Looks like
you lost!
127:
Whoa... *hic*
I'm not moving my legs, but
somehow I'm walking... Isn't that just
*hic* crazy?
131:
Well, we should have seen this
coming. Are you okay to keep
carrying her, Luca?
137:
Wh-why would I be jealous of
something like that?!
141:
Because you secretly want to carry
her yourself. I'm not letting you,
though, so don't get your hopes up.
143:
You're a lot more blunt than I
expected, you know that?
147:
Waves! I hear waves!
That means... *hic* The sea!
Sea, sea, sea, yaaaaay!
152:
Ahh, nice and cool! Just what I need
to clear my head... *hic*
158:
Huh... You can't really see the stars
here.
160:
Too much light from the town
nearby... Well. It's not as bad as
Tokyo, at least.
165:
Marina... What kind of a man was
my father?
168:
After all this time, why did he just
now call out to me? It's not like I'm
special in any way...
177:
That's the type of man he was. He
didn't trust a single soulnot his
crew, not his friends... But he still
didn't want to let them go.
179:
The crewmates that died, the family
he left behind... I'm sure all he
wanted was to have them back and
by his side.
187:
But you should make sure to hold on
to that kindness, and save it for
when someone you truly care for
comes along.
193:
I'll be heading home tomorrow. To
see my mother.
197:
Hmm. That seems like the right thing
to do.
202:
Alk, what do you think... If I asked her
to let me join the Crimson Blades,
would she?
208:
In that case, I'm definitely not letting
you carry her. Let me enjoy this last
little moment with her.
213:
Grab on to me again, Marina. I'll take
you back to the inn.
217:
Hmm, I dunno about that... What
kind of a lesson would I be teaching
you then?
